burg
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a place, locality; town; in 1976 cit `house'
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: an Americanism, consolidated for a time in active NZ usage by the influence of the `talkies'. I can remember it as a very popular slang word at Havelock School, ca1935-1940, but I have since heard it only occasionally used (and then only humorously) since.
